I" <p>Just like <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/streams-formalize-input-output">streams help with I/O</a> and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/promises-streamline-asynchronous-processing">promises help with asynchronous processing</a>, exceptions help with error handling. Through the try-catch pattern, many languages enable error handling at runtime, as a usual part of software operation.</p>
